+| A-037 | 005C stores successful reference generation as `application_status = reference_generated` even though the data-model enum table omits that value, because the screen source explicitly says the application status changes to `Reference Generated` when completeness passes and the official `LO...` number is generated. | Source documents conflict: `screen-spec.md` S12 names the output status, while `data-model.md` §28 lists later lifecycle statuses but not `reference_generated`. The slice needs an auditable transition point before appraisal without inventing document/completeness checks. | `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S12; `docs/source/data-model.md` §13.1 and §28; `docs/source/screen-spec-member-portal.md` MP08 | 005C-reference-number-generation-and-loan-request-register and future completeness/appraisal slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Future completeness/appraisal slices should either confirm `reference_generated` as a canonical stored status or map it into `appraisal_in_progress` after the appraisal workbench is implemented. |
